commit_message:
Switch to use test_utils.call_until_true

test.call_until_true has been deprecated since Newton on Tempest side,
and now Tempest provides test_utils.call_until_true as the stable
library method. So this patch switches to use the stable method before
removing old test.call_until_true on Tempest side.

Change-Id: Idfbd20c31246ec884ad10f9fce42816ce5f15bf3

commit_message:
Fix Kolla gate

There are two issue in kolla gate now. Since source building is voting,
we have to squash these two fixes into one

Disable gpgcheck in grafana repo

Seems there is something wrong in grafana repo gpg key. Disable gpgcheck
until it is fixed

Partial-Bug: #1664272

Add VENV variable in bifrost base Dockerfile

* ANSIBLE_FROM_PYPI is removed in bifrost.
* Only when VENV exist, ansible is installed in global rather then root
  user

Change-Id: Ib96433e6d2a03941cace8ed15dafbb314c4551eb

commit_message:
Let Nova to pick availability zone if more than 1

In the Angular Launch Instance, if there is more than one availability zone,
default to the option for the Nova scheduler to pick.  This is a regression
from the legacy Launch Instance feature.

If you want to simulate testing the logic with multiple avaiability zones,
go to:  .../launch-instance/launch-instance-model.service.js line 785 and add:

model.availabilityZones.push({label: 'another one', value: 'another one'});

(cherry picked from commit be6bcef45289ce1a934db478e5c9c7705890af18)
(cherry picked from commit 821ac9a923dd1250e44df2c4fddef773a27d6e3f)

Conflicts:
	openstack_dashboard/dashboards/project/static/dashboard/project/workflow/launch-instance/details/details.html

Change-Id: Ib81447382bc9d43e33ce97f78c085d2a94ff2018
Closes-Bug: 1613900

commit_message:
Finish switching to decorators.idempotent_id

Most modules are switched to using decorators.idempotent_id and
this patch covers the remaining and removes the old decorator check.

NOTE: The old decorator test.idempotent_id is still necessary to be
      used on the other projects.

Change-Id: Ice7f593fbc109863eba11402c2f3af75fc6ab9a1
Closes-Bug: #1616913

commit_message:
Add E128 to pep8 check list

Unlike E126, which is controversial, E128 is a check should be applied
to code.

E128 continuation line under-indented for visual indent

subject: Use proper horizon version for unit tests
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2017-02-13 14:30:18.000000000', 'files': ['test-requirements.txt'], 'message': 'Use proper horizon version for unit tests

Before, it was installing latest master version for unit tests.
But it is incorrect version of horizon for any of stable branch of our
manila Ui plugin. So, update test-requirements.txt file to install
appropriate branch of Horizon to avoid issues related to evolvement of
latest Horizon that can be incompatible with stable version of plugin.

Change-Id: I2c0a6f283e92c0fb103da211e19228fde46491f8
'}]
commit_message:
Use proper horizon version for unit tests

Before, it was installing latest master version for unit tests.
But it is incorrect version of horizon for any of stable branch of our
manila Ui plugin. So, update test-requirements.txt file to install
appropriate branch of Horizon to avoid issues related to evolvement of
latest Horizon that can be incompatible with stable version of plugin.

Change-Id: I2c0a6f283e92c0fb103da211e19228fde46491f8

commit_message:
Handle log message interpolation by the logger in identity/

interpolated by the logger.

[1]: http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.i18n/guidelines.html#adding-variables-to-log-messages

commit_message:
Update restore status in restore page

When watching the restore page, update (poll?) the restore
status. If a restore is in_progress, user shouldn't refresh
the page to see it is success.

commit_message:
trunk: Add tempest test validating subport connectivity

The patch uses commands over SSH to define VLAN interfaces within
guests.

Test creates two instances with one trunk port and one subport - each
port is on different network. Connectivity is tested
using ping from one instance to the addresses on VLAN interfaces of the
other instance.

Change-Id: Iac801621c19ad488ea6210401f73f76564e4a9d3

commit_message:
Add pypi package 'docker' to requirements

The pypi package 'docker-py' [1] has been renamed to 'docker' [2].
This patch add 'docker' to requirements as a first step to handle
the renaming. Later, we needs to work with all projects that
has reference to 'docker-py' and help them to migrate to the
new package.

[1] https://pypi.python.org/pypi/docker-py
[2] https://pypi.python.org/pypi/docker

Change-Id: Ib66a803653c5c0b92c981612f3788f5ab36dda0d

- Verify .ring.gz path exist if ring file is the first argument.

[{'number': 24, 'created': '2017-02-11 01:32:24.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/tests/contrib/gate_hook.sh', 'neutron/tests/contrib/hooks/dstat', 'tox.ini', 'neutron/tests/contrib/hooks/stack_base'], 'message': 'Enable dstat for in-gate functional and fullstack test runs

This may become handy when debugging gate failures like job or test case
or ovsdb timeouts, to see the load of the machine, as well as to

local.conf [[localrc]], and then call ./stack.sh.

Now that we install some pypi packages into the system, and since

broke failing to locate subunit-2to1 script in the tox env directory. To

commit_message:
Enable dstat for in-gate functional and fullstack test runs

This may become handy when debugging gate failures like job or test case
or ovsdb timeouts, to see the load of the machine, as well as to
understand whether the machine was e.g. locked by its hypervisor during
test run.

Instead of using devstack as a library, we just enable the service in
local.conf [[localrc]], and then call ./stack.sh.

Now that we install some pypi packages into the system, and since
functional targets were using those system packages, post_gate_hook.sh
broke failing to locate subunit-2to1 script in the tox env directory. To
fix that, we disable sitepackages= for all functional tox targets. This
was enabled back in the times when we attempted to install neutron for
the functional job using devstack [1], and we no longer do it, so it
should be ok to stick to all packages from the tox venv.

[1] Icc38cacd69bc5843ccfcc60237a7102df6d8597f

Change-Id: I73857f63f512e26d595c61a20ec5bf22d2fb0da7

The file is not read by any tests, so it's effectively a no-op.

commit_message:
fix create_consistencygroup in xiv

create_consistencygroup failed when extracting extra_specs. This is
due to ConsistencyGroup.volume_type_id having an extra comma at the
end (e.g. u'2ec11e39-881a-4392-a0dd-2254ec4b39a0,').

Change-Id: I52dd2d8c55afccb6734742a7ca4fe916eba0142d

(cherry picked from commit 7487e706426d74555d639146a188618fc1e103f2)

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2017-02-14 03:10:20.000000000', 'files': ['karbor/services/protection/client_factory.py', 'karbor/services/protection/clients/utils.py'], 'message': 'Support clients with privileged user in karbor

In some cases, Karbor services or protection plugins require
clients(cinder/nova) with admin authority to call the RESTAPI
with the rule for admin.

For example: Nova protection plugins from vendor need Nova
client with admin authority to call the RESTAPI about
hypervisor. The tenant karbor can be used to initialize
the clients with admin authority.

Co-authored-by: zengchen <chenzeng2@huawei.com>
Change-Id: I0c59ebabd226f63369ef1038f6be17684491d632

commit_message:
Support clients with privileged user in karbor

In some cases, Karbor services or protection plugins require
clients(cinder/nova) with admin authority to call the RESTAPI
with the rule for admin.

For example: Nova protection plugins from vendor need Nova
client with admin authority to call the RESTAPI about
hypervisor. The tenant karbor can be used to initialize
the clients with admin authority.

Co-authored-by: zengchen <chenzeng2@huawei.com>
Change-Id: I0c59ebabd226f63369ef1038f6be17684491d632
Closes-Bug: #1650239

commit_message:
Remove support for py34

The gating on python 3.4 is restricted to <= Mitaka. This is due
to the change from Ubuntu Trusty to Xenial, where only python3.5
is available. There is no need to continue to keep these settings.

Change-Id: I8899429c4bdbc723c448624be49cc27343798f25

subject: test_dependency: sort retrieved journal rows.
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2017-02-14 01:17:01.000000000', 'files': ['networking_odl/tests/unit/journal/test_dependency_validations.py'], 'message': 'test_dependency: sort retrieved journal rows.

BaseDependencyValidationsTestCase.test_dependency wrongly assumes
the result of db query of journal is sorted. Explicitly sort it
based on seqnum. Otherwise it sometimes successes/fails depending
on what rdbms returns.

Change-Id: I66cbd5e57ae0cfba20caf28609a16486707a22a7
'}]
commit_message:
test_dependency: sort retrieved journal rows.

BaseDependencyValidationsTestCase.test_dependency wrongly assumes
the result of db query of journal is sorted. Explicitly sort it
based on seqnum. Otherwise it sometimes successes/fails depending
on what rdbms returns.

Change-Id: I66cbd5e57ae0cfba20caf28609a16486707a22a7

commit_message:
Fix python monasca-api mysql server connection loss

This patch is a fix for MySQL connection timeouts that ocasionally
occurs on the python monasca-api after not being used for about 8
hours.

Reference for the change:
  http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/rel_0_9/core/pooling.html#pool-setting-recycle

Change-Id: I8186718aead27f7966e3c35dbd0f490884419955
(cherry picked from commit 2f69bf015172964fb4340a35be61d50317a53017)

[5/11] Refactor test_volume file

Due to the situation, that we've already had more that 7000 lines of
code in this file and it contains different test cases, it is
reasonably to divide it into smaller files.

and getting volumes by active window test cases.

subject: Handle log message interpolation by the logger in network/
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2017-02-13 17:14:36.000000000', 'files': ['openstackclient/network/v2/network_segment.py', 'openstackclient/network/v2/router.py', 'openstackclient/network/v2/subnet_pool.py', 'openstackclient/network/v2/subnet.py', 'openstackclient/network/v2/security_group_rule.py'], 'message': 'Handle log message interpolation by the logger in network/

According to OpenStack Guideline[1], logged string message should be
interpolated by the logger.

[1]: http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.i18n/guidelines.html#adding-variables-to-log-messages
Related-Bug: #1596829

commit_message:
Prepare for using standard python tests

Add simple script to setup mysql and postgresql databases, this script
can be run by users during testing and will be run by CI systems for
specific setup before running unit tests. This is exactly what is
currently done by OpenStack CI in project-config.

This allows to change in project-config the python-db jobs to
python-jobs since python-jobs will call this script initially.

See also
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2016-November/107784.html

Needed-By: I141f3a470ccb299ab60f68ec9cef30069d4f2303
Change-Id: I93abcf684b5be97a733cba9c378af721f2c4f557

commit_message:
Add dns_domain field for network_config model

Now value of DNS domain for a cluster is fetched from
/etc/fuel/astute.yaml file on a master node.
If that value changes, new DNS domain will be applied
for an environment in case of its update. This may lead
to unexpected behavior. That's why dns_domain should be stored
in nailgun database for every environment.

Change-Id: I35eeeac9cdc1bb4bb7c93ceda9fff6979b84f382
Closes-Bug: #1641140

commit_message:
Configure the placement API's interface to use the internal endpoint

Due to the keystoneauth library's defaults, it uses the public interface
currently. This is not desirable in most cases (specially when using
network isolation); so we set it to use the internal one.

Change-Id: Ic222a2b734f4d512349fd8556aa2864b13a1eb07
Depends-On: I1c7fd3a32d04e2fafb3820d1c1f221f45c613c83
Closes-Bug: #1663187

Yaml.load() return Python object may be dangerous if
you receive a YAML document from an untrusted source
such as the Internet. The function yaml.safe_load()
limits this ability to simple Python objects like
integers or lists.

Reference:
https://security.openstack.org/guidelines/dg_avoid-dangerous-input-parsing-libraries.html

Change-Id: I1ab176105a52135f0f9efbd2e57619c00c2f5642
'}]
commit_message:
Replaces yaml.load() with yaml.safe_load()

Yaml.load() return Python object may be dangerous if
you receive a YAML document from an untrusted source
such as the Internet. The function yaml.safe_load()
limits this ability to simple Python objects like
integers or lists.

Reference:
https://security.openstack.org/guidelines/dg_avoid-dangerous-input-parsing-libraries.html

Change-Id: I1ab176105a52135f0f9efbd2e57619c00c2f5642

commit_message:
Ensures $keystone_wsgi_script_path right permissions.

Closes-Bug: 1645299

In the case of more restrictive, system-wide umask setting,
directory $keystone_wsgi_script_path may become inaccessible for
web-server resulting in keystone failures.

Change-Id: I4cdc053bb88da0a7c2604ff0b431de57e24b41eb
(cherry picked from commit 4f15fb64b1cb60388efbee75acbfb3b13a8fa1f6)

commit_message:
Force DIB_PYTHON_VERSION to be 2

According to the bug, this is required to build images on RHEL 7.3,
and since we don't support python 3 yet we might as well just set
it for all images on all distros.

Change-Id: I6de108d166924e6b4d63bc3decf1ffbe94b34654
Closes-Bug: 1651285

revisions:

When security group is deleted, rules belongs to that security groups are
automatically deleted by cascade=delete.
So rules need to be deleted explicitly when security group is deleted.
Otherwise stale rules remains.

Closes-Bug: #1663470
Change-Id: I44a07d27e44ef5ff17409163c3194cb47b1eede0
'}]
commit_message:
delete sg rule on sg deletion on ODL neutron northbound

When security group is deleted, rules belongs to that security groups are
automatically deleted by cascade=delete.
So rules need to be deleted explicitly when security group is deleted.
Otherwise stale rules remains.

Closes-Bug: #1663470
Change-Id: I44a07d27e44ef5ff17409163c3194cb47b1eede0

subject: Re-enable tee behavior for image builds
revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2017-02-10 17:15:15.000000000', 'files': ['tripleo_common/tests/image/test_image_builder.py', 'tripleo_common/image/image_builder.py'], 'message': "Re-enable tee behavior for image builds

The previous client-based image builds tee'd the output to both a
log file and stdout.  With the yaml-based image builds we lost that
behavior, which makes for a bad user experience when the console
just seems to sit there for 30 minutes while images build, with no
feedback on what's going on.  In addition, due to the default
openstackclient logging configuration, we don't even see the info
message telling the user which file contains the log output.

This change uses the same method as the instack-undercloud
_run_live_command method to tee the output to both the Python
logger and the log file.  It also ensures that our local logger is
configured such that info level messages will be seen.

Change-Id: I7e17a18a8bc170ea70955c87a84ca401cb44aa19
Closes-Bug: 1653768
Closes-Bug: 1646226
"}]
commit_message:
Re-enable tee behavior for image builds

The previous client-based image builds tee'd the output to both a
log file and stdout.  With the yaml-based image builds we lost that
behavior, which makes for a bad user experience when the console
just seems to sit there for 30 minutes while images build, with no
feedback on what's going on.  In addition, due to the default
openstackclient logging configuration, we don't even see the info
message telling the user which file contains the log output.

This change uses the same method as the instack-undercloud
_run_live_command method to tee the output to both the Python
logger and the log file.  It also ensures that our local logger is
configured such that info level messages will be seen.

Change-Id: I7e17a18a8bc170ea70955c87a84ca401cb44aa19
Closes-Bug: 1653768
Closes-Bug: 1646226

commit_message:
Walk over all objects when doing VIF detach

We apply specific rules when doing VIF attach, do not duplicate them
in vif_detach just walk over all port and portgroup objects.
This also fixes an issue when VIF was attached to port manually
(set vif_port_id key in port.extra) and it is impossible to detach
such VIF via v1/nodes/<node_ident>/vifs API.

Closes-Bug: #1663660

Change-Id: I70fe87bb4ae15a506fec705d10beaed572c0b45e

commit_message:
DVR: Look at all SNAT ports for a subnet match

For IPv6, the csnat port list could have multiple
subnets contained in it, but we were only ever
looking at the one associated with the first fixed
IP when trying to match an internal port.  Change
to check all subnets on all port combinations
(internal and csnat) before giving up.

Change-Id: I9c0ac933c08734a3f6738a233fdf6021ce9bd375
Closes-bug: #1624515

whereas the legacy code sends the show action when the API lists.

commit_message:
Pecan: Fix tags handling for pecan

Tags controller was not being picked up from the extension.  This also
allows the usage of collection_methods that tags uses.  Also, the tags
extension made use of action_status on a resource, which allowed
overriding the default status codes, so this patch handles action_status
as well.

Change-Id: Ic7f5cfddd30f26737469516235053656f1ba6a24

commit_message:
Reduce memcached memory usage

By default memcache will be setup with 95% of the memory available in
the system. We do not need this much memory assigned and it can lead to
OOM killer issues. This change reduces the default configuration to 50%
of the available memory instead.

Change-Id: I21761e7f4d4d732237d8025c756a2f7a13575afa
Partial-Bug: #1662941

commit_message:
Skip unittests of cinder if not related to code

On Cinder gate, today unittests jobs run for patches which is not
related code. That wastes gate resources and developers need to wait
for much time even if they propose doc patches. This patch adds
all-files-match-any like the other projects.

NOTE: This is found during I79074a29eedf083dee21fd1798ed595cbfb2b2b8
      which is the doc change only.

Change-Id: I91e8b1e2af328ed957e1058343a7167cb49e27a2

commit_message:
Allow placement endpoint interface to be set

This patch exposes the "interface" option for ks_filter to allow
the placement API to be connected on a specific endpoint interface.

The previous was to force "public", which is default for keystoneauth.
The default for the placement service mirrors this value.

Change-Id: Ic996e596f8473c0b8626e8d0e92e1bf58044b4f8

commit_message:
Remove a py34 environment from tox

The gating on python 3.4 is restricted to <= Mitaka. This is due to
the change from Ubuntu Trusty to Xenial, where only python3.5 is
available. There is no need to continue to keep these settings.

Change-Id: Id1bc631d1d301a990ae2618e3d081b9b926e1c55

commit_message:
Wrapper for updating Neutron resources

This wrapper enables updating of Neutron resources with arbitrary
resource attributes. A minimum of 1 Neutron resource attribute
(key-value) has to be updated.

Example:

  execute[neutronv2:update_resource_attrs("port",
              "25443f00-1ef4-47fd-b1fa-f494126e196e",
              "admin_state_up", "False")]

Implements: blueprint update-neutron-resources
Change-Id: If382f28f7dc377e4d5d6267fd7f459f1156e975d

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2017-02-04 03:20:17.000000000', 'files': ['migration/manage_migration.py'], 'message': 'Replaces yaml.load() with yaml.safe_load()

Yaml.load() return Python object may be dangerous if you receive
a YAML document from an untrusted source such as the Internet.
The function yaml.safe_load() limits this ability to simple Python
objects like integers or lists.

Reference:
https://security.openstack.org/guidelines/dg_avoid-dangerous-input-parsing-libraries.html

'}]
commit_message:
Replaces yaml.load() with yaml.safe_load()

Yaml.load() return Python object may be dangerous if you receive
a YAML document from an untrusted source such as the Internet.
The function yaml.safe_load() limits this ability to simple Python
objects like integers or lists.

Reference:
https://security.openstack.org/guidelines/dg_avoid-dangerous-input-parsing-libraries.html

Change-Id: I9841e688e16e9bebef5eb278ee2f3a12f2ca61f4

Add simple script to setup mysql and postgresql databases, this script
can be run by users during testing and will be run by CI systems for

See also

Needed-By: I32f02e904d36ed21a22a1e535b35a15318e1ee16

'}]
commit_message:
Prepare for using standard python tests

Add simple script to setup mysql and postgresql databases, this script
can be run by users during testing and will be run by CI systems for
specific setup before running unit tests. This is exactly what is
currently done by OpenStack CI in project-config.

This allows to change in project-config the python-db jobs to
python-jobs since python-jobs will call this script initially.

See also
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2016-November/107784.html

Needed-By: I32f02e904d36ed21a22a1e535b35a15318e1ee16
Change-Id: I70e83ea22be75e6c31428f56c6e68c49976d1eab
(cherry picked from commit 08f2401ddbc8f47f58848224b8638f4eb1a1560b)

commit_message:
Prepare for using standard python tests

Add simple script to setup mysql and postgresql databases, this script
can be run by users during testing and will be run by CI systems for
specific setup before running unit tests. This is exactly what is
currently done by OpenStack CI in project-config.

This allows to change in project-config the python-db jobs to
python-jobs since python-jobs will call this script initially.

See also
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2016-November/107784.html

Needed-By: I32f02e904d36ed21a22a1e535b35a15318e1ee16
Change-Id: I70e83ea22be75e6c31428f56c6e68c49976d1eab

commit_message:
Enable release notes translation

Releasenote translation publishing is being prepared. 'locale_dirs'
needs to be defined in conf.py to generate translated version of the
release notes.

no translations at all - but we add the entry here nevertheless to
prepare for it.

subject: Disable the deprecation warnings as errors for puppet-syntax
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2017-02-13 04:28:15.000000000', 'files': ['Rakefile'], 'message': 'Disable the deprecation warnings as errors for puppet-syntax

Recently puppet4 started deprecating ruby 2.0 with the following
commit: https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppet/commit/e9eda7ed56fddcf185fc155d7e0ae054ea327504

One way to work-around this (in the absence of a more recent ruby
version) is to not treat this deprecation warnings as fatal when
doing the puppet syntax check

Change-Id: If021c5ae7528bced9673923a5ad0027999b79e9b
Related-Bug: #1660943
'}]
commit_message:
Disable the deprecation warnings as errors for puppet-syntax

Recently puppet4 started deprecating ruby 2.0 with the following
commit: https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppet/commit/e9eda7ed56fddcf185fc155d7e0ae054ea327504

One way to work-around this (in the absence of a more recent ruby
version) is to not treat this deprecation warnings as fatal when
doing the puppet syntax check

Change-Id: If021c5ae7528bced9673923a5ad0027999b79e9b
Related-Bug: #1660943

commit_message:
Disable creation of public shares per configuration

Fix [1] for bug [2] disabled creating of public share types
per configuration but did not address the part of the bug
that required disabling of public *share* creation per
configuration.

Fix that here.

[1] Ia3808486b8604270127c22d45e455e1955b36dba
[2] https://bugs.launchpad.net/manila-ui/+bug/1593057

Change-Id: I0c256d0007395e659f804e8874424f4148021ca8
Closes-bug: #1650610
(cherry picked from commit a29fe603141f2552c5fd2971dbd9a246c397448a)

commit_message:
Use proper horizon version for unit tests

Before, it was installing latest master version for unit tests.
But it is incorrect version of horizon for any of stable branch of our
manila Ui plugin. So, update test-requirements.txt file to install
appropriate branch of Horizon to avoid issues related to evolvement of
latest Horizon that can be incompatible with stable version of plugin.

Change-Id: Iadc26ac3997711143ca27de92a25656c96d5416c
Closes-Bug: #1664213

commit_message:
Enforce the verification of repo dict

If user_external_repo is not defined, the complete task should be
skipped. However, ansible checks and borks if the dict doesn't
contain repo, so we add a condition to avoid this.

revisions:
[{'number': 6, 'created': '2017-02-09 18:44:37.000000000', 'files': ['playbooks/roles/bifrost-ironic-install/tasks/get_ipxe.yml', 'releasenotes/notes/ipxe-download-bc1235cbbc87121c.yaml'], 'message': "roles: bifrost-ironic-install: Always download the latest iPXE files

Set the 'force' option in the get_url module to 'yes' to always download
the latest files if necessary. This aims to resolve iPXE problems
related to http://ipxe.org/err/040ee1. One of the solutions suggested
there is to use the latest version of iPXE. However, up to know, we
didn't update the files after the initial download which means that such
problems could persist indefinitely. iPXE files are really small, so
the download overhead is really minimal.

Change-Id: Ib8f7e4d74a33eeb4147732f7e161ba03de434e7b
"}]
commit_message:
roles: bifrost-ironic-install: Always download the latest iPXE files

Set the 'force' option in the get_url module to 'yes' to always download
the latest files if necessary. This aims to resolve iPXE problems
related to http://ipxe.org/err/040ee1. One of the solutions suggested
there is to use the latest version of iPXE. However, up to know, we
didn't update the files after the initial download which means that such
problems could persist indefinitely. iPXE files are really small, so
the download overhead is really minimal.

Change-Id: Ib8f7e4d74a33eeb4147732f7e161ba03de434e7b

commit_message:
Add choices for option '--policy'

When creating server group, the '--policy' option is required, but
valid choice is 'affinity' or 'anti-affinity', adding multiple
policies will produce an error. This patch add choices and default
value for option '--policy', and remove the former help message.

Change-Id: I312680af384363b3e9a7de9aa1f0946643e193e2
Closes-Bug: #1662771

subject: Allow the usage of own repos instead of uca/rdo
revisions:
[{'number': 6, 'created': '2017-02-13 12:50:48.000000000', 'files': ['tasks/pre_install.yml', 'defaults/main.yml'], 'message': "Allow the usage of own repos instead of uca/rdo

If a deployer has a mirror of uca/rdo, it probably wants to use it.
Defining the URL currently works, but that process wouldn't work if
the mirror is using a different key.

This commit keeps the current behavior of using UCA with signing
packages from upstream everywhere, but with this change, you can also
define your own mirror (CentOS/Ubuntu) with your own key.

Change-Id: Icd9c3b6b7b824cb5cb29fd745777e4c6148e6481
Signed-off-by: Jean-Philippe Evrard <jean-philippe.evrard@rackspace.co.uk>
"}]
commit_message:
Allow the usage of own repos instead of uca/rdo

If a deployer has a mirror of uca/rdo, it probably wants to use it.
Defining the URL currently works, but that process wouldn't work if
the mirror is using a different key.

This commit keeps the current behavior of using UCA with signing
packages from upstream everywhere, but with this change, you can also
define your own mirror (CentOS/Ubuntu) with your own key.

Change-Id: Icd9c3b6b7b824cb5cb29fd745777e4c6148e6481
Signed-off-by: Jean-Philippe Evrard <jean-philippe.evrard@rackspace.co.uk>

commit_message:
Remove support for py34

The gating on python 3.4 is restricted to <= Mitaka. This is due
to the change from Ubuntu Trusty to Xenial, where only python3.5
is available. There is no need to continue to keep these settings.

Change-Id: I1100dfbd3af361af33438263771ce7bf45d5bef0

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2017-02-09 12:35:42.000000000', 'files': ['requirements.txt', 'test-requirements.txt'], 'message': "Cleanup python requirements

there are a number of requirements listed in requirements.txt that can
be dropped or moved around, especially since bifrost begins to support
installing/operating ironic on a remote host:

- six - not used directly. Is listed as dependency for os_ironic_facts
  module, but so is shade which requires it anyway.

- Jinja2 - not used directly, is a dependency for Ansible

- Babel - not used directly as no strings use i18n in bifrost inventory,
  and even when they begin to, this should be done through oslo.i18n instead.
  It is also pulled in as oslo.log->oslo.i18n->Babel dependency anyway.

- PyMySQL - not used by bifrost inventory itself, is installed as part of
  bifrost-ironic-install role.

- pycrypto - not used by bifrost itself, but will be installed as Ansible
  dependency

- PyYAML - although used by bifrost inventory, in real usage we
  should better rely on Ansible's dependency on PyYAML for that and use
  whatever version Ansible developers declare as required.
  Moved to test-requirements for running tests without installing
  Ansible.

Change-Id: I8021ec10f82b17590dd86780da6e27589fdea1ba
"}]
commit_message:
Cleanup python requirements

there are a number of requirements listed in requirements.txt that can
be dropped or moved around, especially since bifrost begins to support
installing/operating ironic on a remote host:

- six - not used directly. Is listed as dependency for os_ironic_facts
  module, but so is shade which requires it anyway.

- Jinja2 - not used directly, is a dependency for Ansible

- Babel - not used directly as no strings use i18n in bifrost inventory,
  and even when they begin to, this should be done through oslo.i18n instead.
  It is also pulled in as oslo.log->oslo.i18n->Babel dependency anyway.

- PyMySQL - not used by bifrost inventory itself, is installed as part of
  bifrost-ironic-install role.

- pycrypto - not used by bifrost itself, but will be installed as Ansible
  dependency

- PyYAML - although used by bifrost inventory, in real usage we
  should better rely on Ansible's dependency on PyYAML for that and use
  whatever version Ansible developers declare as required.
  Moved to test-requirements for running tests without installing
  Ansible.

Change-Id: I8021ec10f82b17590dd86780da6e27589fdea1ba

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2017-02-07 23:09:13.000000000', 'files': ['tests/unit/test_osclients.py', 'rally/osclients.py'], 'message': 'Add expected variable to heat.create_client

Closes-Bug: 1661643
This adds the instantiation of "interface" which is a variable expected
by keystoneauth1.adapter but is not provided by
rally.Heat.osclient.create_client. These commits provide the missing
variable and include test units for heatclient.

This issue became apparent after another bug was found (1655728). This
was an issue pertaining to neutron-client but it highlighted the
possibility that this could occur with the other service clients.

The limitations of this code are that it solves the problem ONLY for
heatclient. Somebody needs to go in and investigate whether this issue
is possible for all the other clients (minus neutronclient and
heatclient). This obviously costs time and effort.

Commit messages follow:

osclient: Add ToDo as reminder to revisit issue

The explicit creation of endpoint_type is a short-term solution.
When python-heatclient deprecates endpoint_type, this section of
code should be removed.

osclients: Pass interface variable to heat client

heatclient uses keystoneauth1.adapter which expects the interface
variable. This is the same variable of endpoint_type. The
short-term solution is to provide both endpoint_type (already
included in the previous commit) and interface. See the PR comment
for more proposed solutions.

osclients: Fix ToDo format

osclients: Include interface in ToDo comment

test_osclients: Unit tests for Heat.create_client

A unit test for heat client creation is included.

of instantiated keyword arguments is also included.

Change-Id: I373658e27b357920b8ff6cc38f90459d9623fc9a
'}]
commit_message:
Add expected variable to heat.create_client

Closes-Bug: 1661643
This adds the instantiation of "interface" which is a variable expected
by keystoneauth1.adapter but is not provided by
rally.Heat.osclient.create_client. These commits provide the missing
variable and include test units for heatclient.

This issue became apparent after another bug was found (1655728). This
was an issue pertaining to neutron-client but it highlighted the
possibility that this could occur with the other service clients.

The limitations of this code are that it solves the problem ONLY for
heatclient. Somebody needs to go in and investigate whether this issue
is possible for all the other clients (minus neutronclient and
heatclient). This obviously costs time and effort.

Commit messages follow:

osclient: Add ToDo as reminder to revisit issue

The explicit creation of endpoint_type is a short-term solution.
When python-heatclient deprecates endpoint_type, this section of
code should be removed.

osclients: Pass interface variable to heat client

heatclient uses keystoneauth1.adapter which expects the interface
variable. This is the same variable of endpoint_type. The
short-term solution is to provide both endpoint_type (already
included in the previous commit) and interface. See the PR comment
for more proposed solutions.

osclients: Fix ToDo format

revisions:
[{'number': 15, 'created': '2017-02-13 11:11:03.000000000', 'files': ['scripts/ansible-pip-str.py', 'scripts/install-ansible-source.sh', '.gitignore', 'releasenotes/notes/ocata-summary-040e557460bab2bc.yaml', 'releasenotes/notes/ansible-pip-install-2b66bd82ce9ed4f6.yaml', 'README.rst', 'scripts/install-ansible-pip.sh', 'playbooks/roles/bifrost-prep-for-install/tasks/main.yml', 'scripts/env-setup.sh', 'scripts/test-bifrost.sh'], 'message': 'Always install Ansible with pip

Instaling and using Ansible from source for bifrost has several
drawbacks, mainly due to how Ansible's 'ansible/hacking/env-setup'
script mangles with PATH and PYTHONPATH, which complicates running it as
part of other scripts. Besides, cloning the whole repo and it's
submodules is somewhat longer.

The main reason why we were doing that at all was a necessity to install
some additional Ansible modules from newer Ansible versions, which we
dropped right into the source of Ansible code - but this does not have to
be so.

Luckily for us, all Ansible versions we target to support can load
modules from 'library' directory next to playbooks/roles,
and we already use that for 'os_ironic_facts' module.
The need to install a particular module can be assessed by running
ad-hoc 'ansible' command against localhost with the module in question
and without any arguments ('ansible localhost -m <module>'):
- if the module is available in Ansible, the stderr will contain
  "changed" substring (as part of the standard module output)
- if the module is absent form Ansible, "changed" string will be absent
  from stderr too, in which case we can download the module from github
  directly into 'playbooks/library' directory.

This patch removes possibility of installing Ansible from source, and
always installs a released Ansible version via pip.
If not installed into venv, Ansible will be installed in user's ~/.local
directory via 'pip install --user'.
The missing but needed modules are downloaded as described above.

Some level of backward compatibility is provided:
- when the ANSIBLE_GIT_BRANCH has form of 'stable-X.Y', the
  env-setup.sh script will do the next best thing and install latest
  available Ansible version of X.Y.w.z

Also, ANSIBLE_PIP_VERSION can now accept a full pip version specifier:
- if ANSIBLE_PIP_VERSION starts with a digit, this exact version will be
  installed (as 'ansible==X.Y.W.Z')
- otherwize this whole variable is assigned as Ansible version specifier
  for pip, e.g

    env ANSIBLE_PIP_VERSION="<2.2" env-setup.sh

  will result in pip being called as

    pip install -U "ansible<2.2"

Closes-Bug: #1663562
Change-Id: I2c9f47abbbb6740d03978f684ad2c876749655b7
'}]
commit_message:
Always install Ansible with pip

Instaling and using Ansible from source for bifrost has several
drawbacks, mainly due to how Ansible's 'ansible/hacking/env-setup'
script mangles with PATH and PYTHONPATH, which complicates running it as
part of other scripts. Besides, cloning the whole repo and it's
submodules is somewhat longer.

The main reason why we were doing that at all was a necessity to install
some additional Ansible modules from newer Ansible versions, which we
dropped right into the source of Ansible code - but this does not have to
be so.

Luckily for us, all Ansible versions we target to support can load
modules from 'library' directory next to playbooks/roles,
and we already use that for 'os_ironic_facts' module.
The need to install a particular module can be assessed by running
ad-hoc 'ansible' command against localhost with the module in question
and without any arguments ('ansible localhost -m <module>'):
- if the module is available in Ansible, the stderr will contain
  "changed" substring (as part of the standard module output)
- if the module is absent form Ansible, "changed" string will be absent
  from stderr too, in which case we can download the module from github
  directly into 'playbooks/library' directory.

This patch removes possibility of installing Ansible from source, and
always installs a released Ansible version via pip.
If not installed into venv, Ansible will be installed in user's ~/.local
directory via 'pip install --user'.
The missing but needed modules are downloaded as described above.

Some level of backward compatibility is provided:
- when the ANSIBLE_GIT_BRANCH has form of 'stable-X.Y', the
  env-setup.sh script will do the next best thing and install latest
  available Ansible version of X.Y.w.z

Also, ANSIBLE_PIP_VERSION can now accept a full pip version specifier:
- if ANSIBLE_PIP_VERSION starts with a digit, this exact version will be
  installed (as 'ansible==X.Y.W.Z')
- otherwize this whole variable is assigned as Ansible version specifier
  for pip, e.g

    env ANSIBLE_PIP_VERSION="<2.2" env-setup.sh

  will result in pip being called as

    pip install -U "ansible<2.2"

Closes-Bug: #1663562
Change-Id: I2c9f47abbbb6740d03978f684ad2c876749655b7

commit_message:
Enable filtering for Cinder LVM volumes

Currently the default behavior of LVM is
to scan all available block devices in
/dev folder, this leads to issues on environments
with Cinder LVM volumes. Guest's volumes are recognized
by parent host's OS and are scanned by LVM. If guest's
volume contains LVM inside, it is also detected by
parent host's OS. Such volumes can not be
deleted.

This patch modifies LVM filter on Cinder node in
order to exclude LVs present in Cinder volume group
from LVM scan. During testing it was found that
initramds should be updated upon changing of filtering
rules.

Change-Id: I49e286e92095259e0196b6dd49dc10da0ebb4c20
Closes-Bug: #1645624
(backported from commit fea0daea1b40e101d978762c23d88183e2b1feb8)

commit_message:
Using sys.exit(main()) instead of main()

As we known, Exceptions are raised by the sys.exit() function.
When they are not handled, no stack traceback is printed in the Python interpreter.

In this patch we have known main() got return values(eg:0, 1), but it can't
specifies exit status when terminate the main thread by unusing sys.exit().
So when using sys.exit(main()) instead of main() may be more readable and
reasonable.

Change-Id: I6b472e0eb2fceb49bb506785f5188e023e1d3968

commit_message:
pbr.version.VersionInfo needs package name (oslo.xyz and not oslo_xyz)

 We need to pass into VersionInfo what one would expect from running:
 setup.py --name

 Right now we pass in say oslo_context and pbr fails if there is no .git in
  the python source tree

  Closes-Bug: #1662266

Change-Id: I45d2edddfd516f65e1589e9b7816f1256e3f0d24

commit_message:
Add helper for driver to check if it owns router

This adds a helper that an L3 service provider can use to check
if a given router_id is associated with it. This makes skipping
events unrelated to the driver simple calls. See dependent patches
for examples.

Related: blueprint multi-l3-backends
Change-Id: I3ecb935722dd7fe75f73ad410225ff1b93b0f605

subject: Restore V3 Diagnostics info
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2017-02-13 15:17:16.000000000', 'files': ['specs/pike/approved/restore-vm-diagnostics.rst'], 'message': "Restore V3 Diagnostics info

Previously approved: Ocata

Changes since Ocata:

1. Type of field 'driver' was changed from string to enum string with
following values: 'libvirt', 'xenapi', 'vmwareapi', 'hyperv', 'ironic'.

2. New fields were added:

* 'utilisation' for CPU.
* 'rx_rate' and 'tx_rate' for NIC.

These fields were added because Xen and VmWare drivers can't provide
some information (e.g 'time' for CPU and 'rx_octets', 'rx_errors', etc
for NIC). But these drivers can provide other information instead.
New fields were added to store this information.

bp restore-vm-diagnostics

APIImpact

Change-Id: Ibcc2b98ae5b3731a9e5a1a3f28fc7ce4655c8ea6
"}]
commit_message:
Restore V3 Diagnostics info

Previously approved: Ocata

Changes since Ocata:

1. Type of field 'driver' was changed from string to enum string with
following values: 'libvirt', 'xenapi', 'vmwareapi', 'hyperv', 'ironic'.

2. New fields were added:

* 'utilisation' for CPU.
* 'rx_rate' and 'tx_rate' for NIC.

These fields were added because Xen and VmWare drivers can't provide
some information (e.g 'time' for CPU and 'rx_octets', 'rx_errors', etc
for NIC). But these drivers can provide other information instead.
New fields were added to store this information.

bp restore-vm-diagnostics

APIImpact

Change-Id: Ibcc2b98ae5b3731a9e5a1a3f28fc7ce4655c8ea6

subject: Add quantum-network-service as a mandatory service
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2017-02-09 15:20:52.000000000', 'files': ['hooks/quantum-network-service-relation-broken', 'hooks/neutron_utils.py'], 'message': 'Add quantum-network-service as a mandatory service

The quantum-network-service relation with nova-cc needs to
be present otherwise metadata server has no keystone auth
credentials. This change adds it to REQUIRED_INTERFACES
so that its absence is reported in workload status. Also
the quantum-network-service-relation-broken symlink has
been added to trigger an assess status call when the
relation is removed.

Change-Id: I9859d532e1ef3c18c8c24308a115624035ef6d0f
Closes-Bug: 1634106
'}]
commit_message:
Add quantum-network-service as a mandatory service

The quantum-network-service relation with nova-cc needs to
be present otherwise metadata server has no keystone auth
credentials. This change adds it to REQUIRED_INTERFACES
so that its absence is reported in workload status. Also
the quantum-network-service-relation-broken symlink has
been added to trigger an assess status call when the
relation is removed.

Change-Id: I9859d532e1ef3c18c8c24308a115624035ef6d0f
Closes-Bug: 1634106

commit_message:
Fix Windows SMB helper

The Windows SMB driver inherits the Generic driver, reusing most
of its logic.

The following change broke the Windows SMB driver and helpers,
changing a few method signatures and return values:
I6e7eca54725d1aef994d617f253e73909a9d8303

This patch fixes the Windows SMB helper based on the above mentioned
change.

Closes-Bug: #1663300

Change-Id: I1ce56ba8abaddda1bf3f0b885f72ad713f36de56

commit_message:
Add tracepath commands to the AIO

The tracepath command is sometimes missing from the gate image.
This PR simply makes sure that the packages for tracepath are
installed so that we get the needed data in the gate at all times.

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2017-02-10 15:42:47.000000000', 'files': ['ironic_inspector/test/unit/test_swift.py', 'ironic_inspector/common/swift.py'], 'message': 'Pass session directly to swiftclient

since v3.2.0 swiftclient supports instantiating the API client from
keystonauth session, and we already require this version as minimal in
ironic.

This patch removes existing workarounds in SwiftAPI code which were there
only to accomodate for absence of session handling in swiftclient,
and now the keystoneauth session built from the [swift] config section
is used directly to instantiate the swift API client.

Change-Id: I593156d122db62b49e2d383d3dbbbae691b7b904
Related-Bug: #1518938
Co-Authored-By: Pavlo Shchelokovskyy <shchelokovskyy@gmail.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Pass session directly to swiftclient

since v3.2.0 swiftclient supports instantiating the API client from
keystonauth session, and we already require this version as minimal in
ironic.

This patch removes existing workarounds in SwiftAPI code which were there
only to accomodate for absence of session handling in swiftclient,
and now the keystoneauth session built from the [swift] config section
is used directly to instantiate the swift API client.

Change-Id: I593156d122db62b49e2d383d3dbbbae691b7b904
Related-Bug: #1518938
Co-Authored-By: Pavlo Shchelokovskyy <shchelokovskyy@gmail.com>

subject: Correct error in Infiniband release note
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2017-02-13 13:20:17.000000000', 'files': ['releasenotes/notes/add_mellanox_hardware_manager-edfae87964737df1.yaml'], 'message': 'Correct error in Infiniband release note

The release note says that a MAC and Client-ID are calculated for
Infiniband nodes according to RFC 4390, but RFC 4390 actually says
'"chaddr" (client hardware address) field MUST be zeroed.' (see
https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4390#page-2). This commit changes the
release note to say "a Mellanox-specific translation", which matches the
comments in hardware_managers/mlnx.py.

Change-Id: I16e70450cecaebb81b5851bb9589bd17a544668b
'}]
commit_message:
Correct error in Infiniband release note

The release note says that a MAC and Client-ID are calculated for
Infiniband nodes according to RFC 4390, but RFC 4390 actually says
'"chaddr" (client hardware address) field MUST be zeroed.' (see
https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4390#page-2). This commit changes the
release note to say "a Mellanox-specific translation", which matches the
comments in hardware_managers/mlnx.py.

Change-Id: I16e70450cecaebb81b5851bb9589bd17a544668b

commit_message:
Allow locust benchmarks to use zeromq

The locust benchmarks currently produce this warning:

    UserWarning: WARNING: Using pure Python socket RPC implementation
    instead of zmq. If running in distributed mode, this could cause a
    performance decrease. We recommend you to install the pyzmq python
    package when running in distributed mode.

http://docs.locust.io/en/latest/installation.html#installing-zeromq

Change-Id: Ib5a0459f9f5fd74cfb2cf053417753edefc9c2b0

commit_message:
Update introspection command to introspect only manageable nodes

With the Newton and later releases, it is possible to introspect
only nodes in the manageable state rather than run bulk
introspection that would work on all imported nodes.

Change-Id: Ic36dea3f93e84ab49731996a69a9d3c28f973e86

commit_message:
Remove py34 env from tox

The gating on python 3.4 is restricted to <= Mitaka. This is due to
the change from ubuntu Trusty to Xenial, where only python 3.5 is
available. There's no need to continue to keep it.

Change-Id: Ia254a7b9e143cf8e5e9d39e3594b8d3a4ce507a4

commit_message:

Add `--keep-running` flag to undercloud deploy

When the deploy fails, it's useful to keep the client running for
debugging. This will allow for querying the heat stack before it's
destroyed.

commit_message:
Find a node by multiple attributes

This patch modifies current attributes matching from a single
name-value->node hit to a best-match score.

Also using an UUID as the attributes table primary key to allow exposing
attributes in API later (bug 1525231).

Change-Id: I205e31652b21b9e030b9530149e533b29c52a387
Closes-Bug: 1651719
Partial-Bug: 1525231

Commit c18f9f7 removed the logging (to debug) of each message received

being used by strutils.mask_password() to sanitize passwords in the
log was slow (#1408362).  mask_password() was subsequently updated to

commit_message:
Restore debug logging of each message in AMQPListener

Commit c18f9f7 removed the logging (to debug) of each message received
by AMQPListener.  This was done for performance reasons, as the regexp
being used by strutils.mask_password() to sanitize passwords in the
log was slow (#1408362).  mask_password() was subsequently updated to
have better performance, so now this change restores the logging,
though with an extra check to ensure that there's no overhead
(mask_password() never called) unless the log level is set to DEBUG.

Change-Id: Id3384f7606f628f33757f6cc9d4768fa0aa4da33
Related-Bug: #1408362

commit_message:
Add optional Sphinx build verification

We need a simple, togglable way to verify that Sphinx has, at a
minimum, generated each of the files outlined within the
`artcl_create_docs_payload.table_of_contents` and added them to
the resulting index.html

- Add togglable var to collect-logs role, `artcl_verify_sphinx_build`
  default to false
- Update artcl_collect_dir to pull from common/defaults

Change-Id: I76fef28a026730818d44274ab01741034f9fa40d

commit_message:
Add a NFV VDU profile in contrib

This profile is a copy of nova server profile.
Enhancement:
- Add security_group property to networks
- Add floating_network_id/floating_ip_address properties to networks
- Create ports before creating instance
- Store port_ids in node.data['internal_ports'] for deletion
- Use jinja2 to handle user_data

TODO:
- handle rebuild
- handle volumes

Change-Id: If34ddab86262f37645a0d1e9b494448eb3197c51

commit_message:
Remove dependency on memory heavy python-requests.

It turns out that Neutron uses python-requests on just one place
and for no good reason. Given that loading Requests amount for 80MB
of RAM in my system, maybe it's worth removing our dependency on
requests.

Change-Id: I905252a55bd174ff1aa8bdec42fe32432746846f

subject: new localrc set strategy
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2017-02-10 21:59:30.000000000', 'files': ['devstack/dsconf.py', 'devstack/tests/test_localconf_set_local.py', 'devstack/tests/test_localconf_merge.py'], 'message': "new localrc set strategy

the localrc is really just executable shell, which means there are
tons of edgecases where you can't treat it the same as simple
assignment a=b.

Instead of trying to be smart about things and reduce duplication in
the localrc files, just do the naive thing and stack up all the shell
declarations in order. When evaluated in shell they will end up
stacking up as expected.

Change-Id: I231d130b24b02cdd79618f85472cee21905884e0
"}]
commit_message:
new localrc set strategy

the localrc is really just executable shell, which means there are
tons of edgecases where you can't treat it the same as simple
assignment a=b.

Instead of trying to be smart about things and reduce duplication in
the localrc files, just do the naive thing and stack up all the shell
declarations in order. When evaluated in shell they will end up
stacking up as expected.

Change-Id: I231d130b24b02cdd79618f85472cee21905884e0

commit_message:
[APIv2] Update registry images tagging

The endpoint of image tag should be changed to follow guidelines
on tag[*]. Main ideas are:
1. To add, remove, or change tags, a PUT request should be sent to
   the root tags URL, the server responds with a 200 status code.
2. To delete the entire tag list associated with a resource, a
   DELETE request must be sent to the root tags URL.
3. the resource identified by URL must expose its tags with root
   URL like: http://example.com:8386/servers/1234567890/tags.
4. There also add a get tags method and a dozen of unit test

*: http://specs.openstack.org/openstack/api-wg/guidelines/tags.html

Partial-Implements: bp v2-api-experimental-impl
Change-Id: Ia70322538f966ad032ae804c99f6f07463461e7d

subject: placement: switch public endpoint on NovaPlacementInternal
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2017-02-13 01:47:02.000000000', 'files': ['puppet/services/nova-placement.yaml'], 'message': "placement: switch public endpoint on NovaPlacementInternal

Nova Compute needs access to Nova Placement endpoint.
It seems that Nova is using the publicURL to reach the API.
In the case of IPv6 deployment where Public endpoints are binded to IPv6
addressed, compute nodes can't reach them.

This patch switches Nova Placement publicURL endpoint to use Internal
network, that way, we're sure nova-compute and nova-schedule will reach
the endpoint through internal network.

Moreover, there is no point of exposing Nova Placement API on public
network since the service is only used by the internal Cloud (Nova).

Closes-Bug: #1663187
Change-Id: I5d69fc76ac0c9cf872402af83f06eb40ec694d5b
"}]
commit_message:
placement: switch public endpoint on NovaPlacementInternal

Nova Compute needs access to Nova Placement endpoint.
It seems that Nova is using the publicURL to reach the API.
In the case of IPv6 deployment where Public endpoints are binded to IPv6
addressed, compute nodes can't reach them.

This patch switches Nova Placement publicURL endpoint to use Internal
network, that way, we're sure nova-compute and nova-schedule will reach
the endpoint through internal network.

Moreover, there is no point of exposing Nova Placement API on public
network since the service is only used by the internal Cloud (Nova).

Closes-Bug: #1663187
Change-Id: I5d69fc76ac0c9cf872402af83f06eb40ec694d5b

commit_message:
Re-order imports to comply with OpenStack Style Guidelines

According to Openstack import order template[1], stdlib imports,
third-party imports and project imports should be separated into
different code blocks.

[1] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/hacking/#import-order-template

Co-Authored-By: hujie <mike.hu@huawei.com>

Change-Id: Id094fb697f4f4eadfb1e73cfcfa4a3ac3f7bc306

commit_message:
Bump the LAST_KNOWN_API_VERSION to 29 in OSC

The command to inject NMI has been merged for OSC [0] but the API version
required for it hasn't been bumped. This patch fixes the problem.

Note that this patch has not been cherry-picked, that's because this
problem has been fixed by another patch [1] in the master branch which
is bumping the maximum version to 31.

[0] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/357661/
[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/418359/

Closes-Bug: #1662959
Change-Id: I285178d0b7384956eb151ca66007d7354566574d

revisions:

We statically configure the host IP for many networks during the
bootstrap AIO process. Later, when the inventory is generated,
we use an IP from the queue, which could be conflicting with the

This should fix it.

Change-Id: I5a49eebef48892d7266684f1ffdbe1d08d82c211

commit_message:
Ensures the host IP isn't used for containers

We statically configure the host IP for many networks during the
bootstrap AIO process. Later, when the inventory is generated,
we use an IP from the queue, which could be conflicting with the
host (Probability: 1 on 204).

This should fix it.

Change-Id: I5a49eebef48892d7266684f1ffdbe1d08d82c211
(cherry picked from commit 96c766004de478f08026754e3d0443ebf8b6f467)

commit_message:
Add group vars to enable integration with barbican

Add group variables, 'nova_barbican_enabled' and
'cinder_barbican_enabled', that will be set dependent on the
availability of barbican hosts within an environment and enable
integration of barbican with nova and cinder.

subject: Fix alarm_count with multiple group_by fields from CLI
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2017-02-07 21:11:46.000000000', 'files': ['monasca_tempest_tests/tests/api/test_alarms_count.py', 'monasca_api/v2/reference/alarms.py'], 'message': "Fix alarm_count with multiple group_by fields from CLI

CLI sends multiple group_by fields with ',' as a separator, but the
',' gets urlencoded. Falcon then treats the group_by parameter
as a string instead of a list so 'state,severity' was treated as a
single value and failed validation. The fix was to do a split using ','.
The tempest tests did not urlencode the ',' so Falcon treated
group_by as a list and the tests succeeded even though the
same test through the CLI would fail.

Created tempest test that shows the failure and that it now works

Change-Id: Ice01df6e66c6b019270fed27de08de8ee713114f
"}]
commit_message:
Fix alarm_count with multiple group_by fields from CLI

CLI sends multiple group_by fields with ',' as a separator, but the
',' gets urlencoded. Falcon then treats the group_by parameter
as a string instead of a list so 'state,severity' was treated as a
single value and failed validation. The fix was to do a split using ','.
The tempest tests did not urlencode the ',' so Falcon treated
group_by as a list and the tests succeeded even though the
same test through the CLI would fail.

Created tempest test that shows the failure and that it now works

Change-Id: Ice01df6e66c6b019270fed27de08de8ee713114f

commit_message:
Add libpq-dev to install os_tempest plugins

We were getting errors locally [0] that complained about libpq-dev not
being installed. This was causing os_tempest plugins installations
to fail, snowballing the run.

This commit adds libpq-dev to the ubuntu 16.04 variables so that we
ensure it's installed before we get to that step.

[0] http://cdn.pasteraw.com/1sdkssty5uvgq315hj7g5lvwpm8xyob

Change-Id: I82eb012ac9d3a630e072e6b873419b86fa39333b
(cherry picked from commit 65c9c1d5ecc59bad7bbaa643039bb5b39489a892)
